Fear is setting in over primary schools resuming at full capacity and with daily attendance. Some teachers are saying schools are nowhere near ready. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Fear is setting in over primary schools resuming at full capacity and with daily attendance. Some teachers are saying schools are nowhere near ready while parents are afraid for their children's health. READ: Primary school pupils to return to class daily from 26 July The Basic Education Department recently gazetted that from 26 July, primary school pupils must return to class every day. The department's decision comes at a time when the third wave has hit four provinces already. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.